column4: Doubled-up (i.e., living with another family) is the primary nighttime residence of the person at the time they were identified as homeless

Unsheltered (e.g. cars, parks, campgrounds, temporary trailers including FEMA trailers, or abandoned buildings) is the primary nighttime residence of the person at the time they were identified as homeless
Hotels/Motels is the primary nighttime residence of the person at the time they were identified as homeless
A Shelter is the primary nighttime residence of the person at the time they were identified as homeless
Shelters or Transitional Housing is the primary nighttime residence of the person at the time they were identified as homeless
Transitional Housing is the primary nighttime residence of the person at the time they were identified as homeless
